    "body": "@gwuillou Can you provide a reproducible example that shows the problem?\n\nAs I cannot reproduce it:\n\n```\nIn [48]: idx = pd.date_range('2013-10-27 01:00', '2013-10-27 04:00', freq='15min', tz='Europe/Zurich')\n\nIn [50]: idx_naive = idx.tz_localize(None)\n\nIn [51]: idx_naive\nOut[51]: \nDatetimeIndex(['2013-10-27 01:00:00', '2013-10-27 01:15:00',\n               '2013-10-27 01:30:00', '2013-10-27 01:45:00',\n               '2013-10-27 02:00:00', '2013-10-27 02:15:00',\n               '2013-10-27 02:30:00', '2013-10-27 02:45:00',\n               '2013-10-27 02:00:00', '2013-10-27 02:15:00',\n               '2013-10-27 02:30:00', '2013-10-27 02:45:00',\n               '2013-10-27 03:00:00', '2013-10-27 03:15:00',\n               '2013-10-27 03:30:00', '2013-10-27 03:45:00',\n               '2013-10-27 04:00:00'],\n              dtype='datetime64[ns]', freq='15T')\n\nIn [52]: idx_naive.tz_localize('Europe/Zurich')\n...\nAmbiguousTimeError: Cannot infer dst time from Timestamp('2013-10-27 02:00:00'), try using the 'ambiguous' argument\n\nIn [53]: idx_naive.tz_localize('Europe/Zurich', ambiguous='infer')\nOut[53]: \nDatetimeIndex(['2013-10-27 01:00:00+02:00', '2013-10-27 01:15:00+02:00',\n               '2013-10-27 01:30:00+02:00', '2013-10-27 01:45:00+02:00',\n               '2013-10-27 02:00:00+02:00', '2013-10-27 02:15:00+02:00',\n               '2013-10-27 02:30:00+02:00', '2013-10-27 02:45:00+02:00',\n               '2013-10-27 02:00:00+01:00', '2013-10-27 02:15:00+01:00',\n               '2013-10-27 02:30:00+01:00', '2013-10-27 02:45:00+01:00',\n               '2013-10-27 03:00:00+01:00', '2013-10-27 03:15:00+01:00',\n               '2013-10-27 03:30:00+01:00', '2013-10-27 03:45:00+01:00',\n               '2013-10-27 04:00:00+01:00'],\n              dtype='datetime64[ns, Europe/Zurich]', freq='15T')\n```\n"
